race.comment: BLACK BABYLON (1) broke through for his Maiden win over 1800m at Hawkesbury. He'd raced at Group level before the spell and resumed over a mile with a promising effort.  The step up in trip is ideal, and he looks well placed against these to repeat. KONING (2) led and held on to place at Hawkesbury over 1800m in a 64. The longer journey is a query, but he's hard-fit now and can make the finish. THINK ROMANCE (3) did a good job last start to finish third over 1900m at Newcastle. That was an improved effort, and the on-pacer also has quinella claims. COOL DRINKS (8) didn't finish it off at Hawkesbury behind the top selection. Fourth up now, and we're likely to see more from him.
